**React re-renders child when parent renders** — default behavior.

**Common causes:**

| Cause | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| New object/array literal as prop | `useMemo` to stabilize |
| Inline function as prop | `useCallback` to stabilize |
| No memoization on component | Wrap in `React.memo` |
| Context value recreated each render | Memoize context value |
| State lifted too high | Move state closer to consumer |

**Quick fixes:**

```jsx
// Memoize component
const Child = React.memo(({ onClick, data }) => { ... });

// Stabilize function prop
const handleClick = useCallback(() => doThing(id), [id]);

// Stabilize object prop
const config = useMemo(() => ({ color, size }), [color, size]);
```

**Root cause check:** `React.memo` does shallow prop compare. New reference = re-render, even if value same. Primitives (`string`, `number`, `bool`) safe. Objects/arrays/functions — must stabilize reference.

**Debug tool:** React DevTools Profiler → "Why did this render?" shows exact prop that changed.

CORS errors mean browser blocked a request because the server didn't permit your origin.

**Common causes + fixes:**

| Cause | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| Server missing `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header | Add header on server: `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` or specific origin |
| Preflight `OPTIONS` request not handled | Server must respond to `OPTIONS` with correct headers |
| Credentials + wildcard origin | Can't use `*` with `credentials: 'include'` — must specify exact origin |
| Wrong port/protocol counts as different origin | `localhost:3000` ≠ `localhost:5000` |
| Proxy not configured in dev | Add proxy in `vite.config.js` / `webpack` / `package.json` |

**Quick server-side fix (Express example):**
```js
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', 'https://yoursite.com');
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type, Authorization');
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS');
  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') return res.sendStatus(204);
  next();
});
```

**Dev shortcut** — proxy requests so browser never sees cross-origin:
```js
// vite.config.js
server: { proxy: { '/api': 'http://localhost:3001' } }
```

CORS is enforced by the **browser**, not the server — so it only affects browser requests, not curl/Postman. If curl works but browser doesn't, it's definitely CORS.

